test_system.src.nms_entities.abstract_basic_object module¶

class test_system.src.nms_entities.abstract_basic_object.AbstractBasicObject(driver: src.drivers.abstract_http_driver.AbstractHttpDriver, parent_id: int, object_id: int, params: Optional[dict] = None)¶

Bases: abc.ABC

Base class of NMS entities. Encapsulates CRUD operations for various drivers. Can be used to either create a new Entity instance or manage an existing one. If object_id > src.constants.NEW_OBJECT_ID the values of the parameters are loaded from NMS using the passed parent_id and object_id

Parameters

  • driver (AbstractHttpDriver) – an inherited instance of the driver

  • parent_id (int) – ID of the parent object

  • object_id (int) – ID of the object. If ID equals to src.constants.NEW_OBJECT_ID, a new object is created. Otherwise, the parameters are loaded from NMS.

  • params (dict) – a dictionary that contains the parameters of the object. Initial dictionary is not changed.

Raises

src.exceptions.ObjectNotFoundException – if object ID is not found

classmethod create(driver: src.drivers.abstract_http_driver.AbstractHttpDriver, parent_id: int, params: Optional[dict] = None)¶

send_param(param_name: str, param_value: any)¶

  • param_value (any) – the value of the parameter to apply
